{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:24:37.061Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Premium Support**\n\nI've got the `previewProjects` list in front of me, and I see some are tied to `client-001`, the preview account. My initial focus is on designing an insanely premium support experience. My next step involves checking if there's an existing ticket structure that encompasses categories, linked projects and related items.\n\n\n**Refining Ticket Structure**\n\nI'm currently focused on refining the `SupportTicket` structure to better accommodate our premium support needs. My primary thought is to add optional properties like `category` (with predefined values) and `projectId`, to link tickets with specific projects, with the intention of extending the existing `SupportTicket` interface to include these attributes. I am exploring both local and global TypeScript type extensions for a type-safe implementation.\n\n\n**Implementing Fluid Ticket Interface**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the UI, considering how to make the support experience luxurious. I'm leaning toward a highly interactive design within `/portal/support/page.tsx`. Local state or `localStorage` seems ideal to keep the support detail pane synchronized. I'm envisioning a fluid sliding panel layout or side-by-side view within `/portal/support/page.tsx` for easy access. This interface would enable filtering by various ticket attributes like status, category, priority, and linked project, enhancing the user experience significantly.\n\n\n"}}
