{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:31:50.680Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Constructing the Premium View**\n\nI've successfully established the foundational structure. The next phase involves integrating the full premium detail view. This encompasses the back button navigation for easy return and a dedicated Enclave Unauthorized handler to gracefully manage cases where a ticket isn't found, ensuring a smooth user experience.\n\n\n**Developing the Layout**\n\nI'm now building the two-column detailed structure. The design integrates a chat log panel on the left and an SLA parameters card on the right. Further updates include the automated, simulated support replies that integrate with the structured return block. I plan on handling the `handleSendReply` function and the entire return statement in one edit to improve workflow.\n\n\n**Refining the Ticket Updates**\n\nI've just refined the ticket update logic within the support system to handle status changes more efficiently. Now, I'm integrating simulated bot replies based on the ticket category, providing more realistic and context-aware responses, including updated details for AI Operations, Billing and Governance categories. This improvement enhances the user experience by delivering tailored feedback.\n\n\n**Implementing Secure Wire**\n\nI've just added a secure wire feature, ensuring access is strictly controlled. The Sovereign Audit Agent now provides credentials, issuing access credentials post verification. I'm focusing on the integration of NIST AI RMF logs and the use of SGX memory for compliance and auditability. The system now returns updated tickets with \"in_progress\" status and agent replies, along with improved security features.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:31:50.684Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"8buvgm2m","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/portal/support/[id]/page.tsx","old_text":"  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-6 text-white font-mono text-center\">\n      <h2>Sovereign Wire Detail</h2>\n    </div>\n  );","new_text":"  const activeTicket = tickets.find(t => t.id === ticketId);\n\n  const handleSendReply = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!replyText.trim() || !activeTicket) return;\n\n    const currentReply = replyText;\n    setReplyText(\"\");\n    setIsReplying(true);\n\n    const userReply = {\n      sender: \"Alexander Mercer (Client)\",\n      text: currentReply,\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    const updatedReplies = [...(activeTicket.replies || []), userReply];\n    const updatedTickets = tickets.map(t => {\n      if (t.id === ticketId) {\n        return { ...t, replies: updatedReplies, status: t.status === \"resolved\" ? \"in_progress\" : t.status };\n      }\n      return t;\n    }) as ClientSupportTicket[];\n\n    saveTickets(updatedTickets);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      let botText = \"Handshake acknowledged. Our on-call systems engineers are reviewing your trace reports inside the secure sandbox.\";\n      let botSender = \"GFF Support Sentinel\";\n\n      if (activeTicket.category === \"AI Operations\") {\n        botSender = \"Dr. Sarah Vance (Lead Systems Architect)\";\n        botText = \"Analyzing enclave CPU and HSM logs. The cryptographic state is re-asserted and key rotational interlocks are operating nominally. All propagation latency is mitigated (<0.4ms).\";\n      } else if (activeTicket.category === \"Billing\") {\n        botSender = \"Nicolette Durand (Billing & Treasury)\";\n        botText = \"Invoices check completed. Invoice settlement is verified at blockchain consensus block 18290192 under seal 0xDE897FFA.\";\n      } else if (activeTicket.category === \"Governance\" || activeTicket.category === \"Documents\") {\n        botSender = \"Sovereign Audit Agent\";\n        botText = \"Operator credentials verified at Clearance Level IV. The NIST AI RMF logs are compiled successfully within SGX memory. Access credentials issued.\";\n      }\n\n      const botReply = { sender: botSender, text: botText, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() };\n      \n      saveTickets(updatedTickets.map(t => {\n        if (t.id === ticketId) {\n          return { ...t, replies: [...updatedReplies, botReply], status: \"in_progress\" };\n        }\n        return t;\n      }) as ClientSupportTicket[]);\n      \n      setIsReplying(false);\n    }, 1500);\n  };\n\n  if (tickets.length > 0 && !activeTicket) {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"space-y-6 max-w-xl mx-auto p-8 border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 rounded-xl text-center font-mono text-white\">\n        <X className=\"w-12 h-12 text-red-400 mx-auto animate-pulse\" />\n        <h3 className=\"text-sm font-bold uppercase\">Secure Wire Not Authorized</h3>\n        <p className=\"text-xs text-white/50\">This communication enclave ID has either expired, rotated, or does not exist inside your clear session namespace.</p>\n        <button onClick={() => router.push(\"/portal/support\")} className=\"inline-flex h-9 items-center justify-center rounded px-4 bg-white text-black font-semibold text-xs tracking-wider uppercase cursor-pointer\">\n          Return to Comm Hub\n        </button>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n\n  const proj = activeTicket ? previewProjects.find(p => p.id === activeTicket.projectId) : null;\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-6 max-w-[1200px] mx-auto pb-12 select-none text-white font-mono\">\n      <div id=\"detail-header-block\">HEADER BLOCK</div>\n      <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-left\">\n        <div id=\"detail-chat-block\" className=\"lg:col-span-2\">CHAT BLOCK</div>\n        <div id=\"detail-param-block\">PARAM BLOCK</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );"}}}
