{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:35:27.376Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"k44k38se","input":{"summary":"Successfully built the premium Client Support Center at `/portal/support`.\n\n### 1. Architectural Narrative & Visual Metaphor\nWe designed the Support Center as a high-fidelity 'Sovereign Security Tunnel' — a zero-trust, hardware-isolated communications workspace. The theme matches the premium, technical, dark-mode styling of GFF AI, featuring monospace typography, Intel SGX attestation banners, cryptographic conversation signatures, and responsive count-down SLA indicators.\n\n### 2. Multi-Pane Responsive Layout Strategy\n- **Overview Stats**: Quick-glance metrics for Active Wires, average SLA Response Rate, Trust Clearance Level, and Sealed consensus logs.\n- **Left Column**: Integrates text search and multi-factor selection filters (Status, Category, Priority, and Project) over a scrollable card deck.\n- **Right Column (Dynamic Context)**:\n  - If NO ticket is selected: Renders a sleek 'Initialize Support Wire' form to open a support handshake with categories (`Project Delivery`, `AI Operations`, `Billing`, `Documents`, `Access`, `Governance`, `General`), Priority Tiers, Sandbox Project linkage, and descriptive trace logs.\n  - If a ticket IS selected: Swaps the form for a live-updating 'Secure Wire Tunnel' thread showing diagnostic dumps, handshake logs, user message bubble cards, and a text input.\n\n### 3. Interactive Telemetry & State Management\n- Built-in full client-side persistence using safely checking React `localStorage` loops.\n- Ticket creation immediately updates state and selects the new ticket, showing a premium success toast message.\n- **Simulated Chat Replies**: Submitting replies triggers automated, context-specific responses 1.5 seconds later (e.g. Lead Systems Architect Sarah Vance verifying HSM key rotation blocks for 'AI Operations' tickets, or billing audits for 'Billing' tickets), making the site feel highly alive, strategic, and expensive.\n\n### 4. Verification & Clean Code Compliance\n- Verified both `/portal/support` and individual deep-links at `/portal/support/[id]` share the same state and sync replies smoothly.\n- Successfully passed zero-warning ESLint validation and clean project-wide TypeScript type-checking. No landing page files were modified.","verified":true}}}
